  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2284",
  "title": "Release v2.1.0",
  "body": "Hello everyone,\r\n\r\nThis new release is more a revamp of the internal tools and codebase InstantSearch.js to have a good clean base for the next features and future releases 👍 \r\n\r\n**What does it includes?**\r\n\r\n* Upgrade of building tools #2240 \r\n* Run prettier and new eslint config on the codebase\r\n* New release script to allow beta version to be released with ease\r\n\r\nThe main feature of this release was also to allow users using the npm package and a code bundler (webpack, rollup, browserify) to have access to a ES6 modules build that will reduce their final app size a lot.\r\n\r\n**What else is included in the release?**\r\n\r\n* New section on the usage guide to guide you on how to use the ES6 modules build.\r\n* A guide on how to create a no results page.\r\n* A guide on how to plug [opensearch](http://www.opensearch.org/Home)\r\n* A guide on how to create custom widgets without using a connector\r\n* Added a new showcase section of all the widgets on the documentation\r\n* A guide on how to ingrate with Angular2+\r\n\r\n**How can you help?**\r\n\r\nWe have release beta version of the 2.1.0 that you easily install with `$ npm install instantsearch.js@beta` and try it out.\r\n\r\nSend us feedback and issues you have experienced by creating a new issue on this repository.\r\n\r\n🚀",
